A R E S O L U T I O N
Honoring Mahle Behr, LLC on the Centennial of its
Dayton Plant.
WHEREAS, The members of the House of Representatives of the 136th 1
General Assembly of Ohio are pleased to congratulate Mahle Behr, LLC, 2
on the auspicious occasion of the One Hundredth Anniversary of its 3
Dayton Plant; and 4
WHEREAS, Recognition of this prestigious milestone is a fitting 5
tribute to Mahle Behr, for throughout the past century, this fine 6
business’ Dayton plant has attained a remarkable record of service to 7
the area. One of Dayton’s oldest employers and one of the city’s 8
largest manufacturers, the site previously served such companies as 9
the Maxwell Motor Company and the Chrysler Group, and today, the plant 10
makes thermal components for automotive manufacturers for Mahle Behr; 11
and 12
WHEREAS, The success of Mahle Behr is a justifiable source of 13
pride and an outstanding reflection not only on the business itself 14
but also on its astute management and on its hard-working employees. 15
This respected enterprise has earned the gratitude and appreciation of 16
many satisfied customers due to the vision and initiative of its 17
staff, and it is truly deserving of high praise; and 18
WHEREAS, Over the years, Mahle Behr has enhanced the quality of 19
life within Dayton and the surrounding area. We are certain that as 20
this worthy establishment maintains its unwavering dedication to 21
service and achievement, it will continue to prosper and will uphold 22
the tradition of excellence that has long been its hallmark; therefore 23
be it 24
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the House of Representatives of 25

